title: Total softwood , production in Canada 2016
summary: The graph shows the production of softwood in Canada over the year of 2016 .
The data is presented in cubic meters .
According to the graph production of softwood is the highest in March and the lowest in December .
gold: This graph depicts the total softwood production in cubic metres of Canada in 2016 . Production starts at approximately 53000 cubic metres in January and increases to one of its maximum values of 57000 cubic metres in March . The following months show first a slow decrease , but then a sharp decrease in July .
